Ephedra distachya.label: Ephedra distachya
Ephedra distachya.description: Ephedra distachya is a shrub in the family Ephedraceae, about 25 cm to 50 cm high, that grows in southern Europe and parts of western and central Asia. Its local names include somlatha. Wikipedia

Ephedra alata.label: Ephedra alata
Ephedra alata.description: Ephedra alata is a species of Ephedra that is native from Morocco and the Sahara in northern Africa, the Middle East and Western Asia, to Central Asia and Southwest Asia. Wikipedia

Ephedra altissima.label: Ephedra altissima
Ephedra altissima.description:
Ephedra altissima is a species of Ephedra that is native to the Mediterranean region in Southern Europe and North Africa.
The species is cultivated as an ornamental plant. Wikipedia

Ephedra aspera.label: Ephedra aspera
Ephedra aspera.description:
Ephedra aspera is a species of Ephedra known by the common names rough jointfir, boundary ephedra, and pitamoreal.
It is native to the southwestern United States from California to Texas and parts of northern Mexico. Wikipedia

Ephedra californica.label: Ephedra californica
Ephedra californica.description: Ephedra californica is a species of Ephedra, known by the common names California jointfir, California ephedra, desert tea, and cañatillo. Wikipedia

Ephedra fasciculata.label: Ephedra fasciculata
Ephedra fasciculata.description: Ephedra fasciculata is a species of plant in the Ephedraceae family. Common names are Arizona Ephedra, Arizona Jointfir, and Desert Mormon-tea. Wikipedia

Ephedra cutleri.label: Ephedra cutleri
Ephedra cutleri.description:
Ephedra cutleri, the Navajo ephedra or Cutler's jointfir, is a species of Ephedra that is native to the Four Corners area of the Southwestern United States.
The rhizomatous shrubs form erect clumps, .25–1.5 metres tall and 3–5 metres wide. Wikipedia

Ephedra boelckei.label: Ephedra boelckei
Ephedra boelckei.description:
Ephedra boelckei is a species of Ephedra that is native to Argentina.

It was originally described by Fidel Antonio Roig in 1984. It has been placed in section Alatae. Wikipedia

Ephedra foliata.label: Ephedra foliata
Ephedra foliata.description:
Ephedra foliata, with the common name shrubby horsetail, is a species of Ephedra.
The plant is native to Western Asia, the Middle East, and Central Asia, from Egypt to Iran and India. Wikipedia

Ephedra fragilis.label: Ephedra fragilis
Ephedra fragilis.description:
Ephedra fragilis, commonly named the joint pine, is a species of Ephedra that is native to eastern Mediterranean region of southern Europe and Northern Africa.
Its habitats are rocky hills and stone walls, where it grows to 6 feet tall. Wikipedia

Ephedra frustillata.label: Ephedra frustillata
Ephedra frustillata.description:
Ephedra frustillata, the Patagonian ephedra, is a plant species in the genus Ephedra.
The plant is found in Patagonia, southern Argentina.
E. frustillata contains apigeninidin, a 3-deoxyanthocyanidin. Wikipedia

Ephedra funerea.label: Ephedra funerea
Ephedra funerea.description:
Ephedra funerea is a species of Ephedra, known by the common name Death Valley jointfir or Death Valley ephedra.
It is native to the Mojave Desert of California and Nevada. Wikipedia

Ephedra intermedia.label: Ephedra intermedia
Ephedra intermedia.description: Ephedra intermedia, with the Chinese common name of Zhong Ma Huang, is a species of Ephedra that is native to Southwest Asia, the Middle East, Central Asia, and South Asia. Wikipedia

Ephedra nevadensis.label: Ephedra nevadensis
Ephedra nevadensis.description:
Ephedra nevadensis is a species of Ephedra native to dry areas of western North America.
Its range extends west to California and Oregon, east to Texas, and south to Mexico, including areas of the Great Basin, Colorado plateau and desert Southwest. Wikipedia

Ephedra przewalskii.label: Ephedra przewalskii
Ephedra przewalskii.description:
Ephedra przewalskii is a species of Ephedra that is native to northwestern China and Mongolia.

It was originally described by Otto Stapf in 1889 and placed in section Alatae, tribe Tropidolepides. Wikipedia

Ephedra multiflora.label: Ephedra multiflora
Ephedra multiflora.description:
Ephedra multiflora is a species of Ephedra that is native to northern Chile and Argentina.
The plant was originally described by Rodolfo Armando Philippi, later formally published by Otto Stapf in 1887, and placed in section Ephedra sect. Wikipedia

Ephedra strobilacea.label: Ephedra strobilacea
Ephedra strobilacea.description:
Ephedra strobilacea is a species of Ephedra that is native to Central Asia, including east to Afghanistan.
The plant grows at 700–2,500 metres in elevation. Wikipedia

Ephedra trifurca.label: Ephedra trifurca
Ephedra trifurca.description: Ephedra trifurca is a species of Ephedra known by the common names longleaf jointfir and Mexican tea. It is native to many of the northern states of Mexico and the southwestern United States, where it is a resident of desert scrub plant communities. Wikipedia

Ephedra torreyana.label: Ephedra torreyana
Ephedra torreyana.description: Ephedra torreyana, with common names Torrey's jointfir or Torrey's Mormon tea, is a species of Ephedra that is native to the deserts and scrublands of the Southwestern United States and northern Mexico. Wikipedia

Ephedra viridis.label: Ephedra viridis
Ephedra viridis.description: Ephedra viridis, known by the common names green Mormon tea, green ephedra, and Indian tea, is a species of Ephedra. It is indigenous to the Western United States, where it is a member of varied scrub, woodland, desert, and open habitats. Wikipedia

Gnetum africanum.label: Gnetum africanum
Gnetum africanum.description: Gnetum africanum is a vine gymnosperm species found natively throughout tropical Africa. Though bearing leaves, the genus Gnetum are gymnosperms, related to pine and other conifers. Wikipedia

Gnetum.label: Gnetum
Gnetum.description: Gnetum is a genus of about 30-35 species of gymnosperms, the sole genus in the family Gnetaceae and order Gnetales. They are tropical evergreen trees, shrubs and lianas. Unlike other gymnosperms they possess vessel elements in the xylem. Wikipedia

Gnetum gnemon.label: Melinjo
Gnetum gnemon.description: Gnetum gnemon is a species of Gnetum native to southeast Asia and the western Pacific Ocean islands, from Assam south and east through Indonesia and Malaysia to the Philippines and Fiji. They are sometimes called padi oats or paddy oats. Wikipedia

Ephedra (genus).label: Ephedra
Ephedra (genus).description: Ephedra is a genus of gymnosperm shrubs, the only genus in its family, Ephedraceae, and order, Ephedrales. Wikipedia
